article.description: — Tafari Simms scored a career-high 32 points as Milwaukee rolled past IUPUI 94-70 on Friday.
article.headline: Simms scores 32 to carry Milwaukee past IUPUI 94-70
article.linkText: Simms scores 32 to carry Milwaukee past IUPUI 94-70
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- — Tafari Simms scored a career-high 32 points as Milwaukee rolled past IUPUI 94-70 on Friday. Simms shot 10 for 13 from the floor, including 5 of 6 on 3-pointers. DeAndre Gholston had 15 points for Milwaukee (4-2, 3-1 Horizon League). Te’Jon Lucas added 14 points and eight assists. Bobby Harvey had 18 points for the Jaguars (1-3, 0-3). Azariah Seay added 12 points. Jaylen Minnett had 11 points. Marcus Burk, whose 17 points per game entering the contest led the Jaguars, shot only 18% for the game (3 of 17). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
